1
00:01:31,060 --> 00:01:35,000
[Dream of Golden Years]

2
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:39,130
[2002]

3
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:37,870
Sir.

4
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:39,680
I'll take a Grade 9 English

5
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:40,610
listening tape.

6
00:01:40,759 --> 00:01:41,200
Got it.

7
00:01:41,229 --> 00:01:42,430
I'll find one for you.

8
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:51,789
Found it.

9
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:55,560
"Back to the Past"?

10
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:57,759
I wrote it wrong in a rush.

11
00:01:57,759 --> 00:01:59,229
It should be "Back to the Future."

12
00:01:59,229 --> 00:02:00,430
That's a classic movie

13
00:02:00,430 --> 00:02:01,120
made in 1985.

14
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:01,920
It's really good.

15
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:02,680
You want a disk of it?

16
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:04,280
I'd rather go back to the past

17
00:02:05,430 --> 00:02:06,920
than the future.

18
00:02:08,729 --> 00:02:11,009
[Episode 11: The Foreshadowing of Fate]

19
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,870
Alright, come on in!

20
00:02:17,870 --> 00:02:18,870
What do you think?

21
00:02:20,310 --> 00:02:21,470
It's well decorated.

22
00:02:21,470 --> 00:02:22,430
-All of these...
-Wei.

23
00:02:22,430 --> 00:02:22,910
were installed by me.

24
00:02:22,910 --> 00:02:24,520
You've created quite a cozy space.

25
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:25,630
No doubt.

26
00:02:25,710 --> 00:02:26,710
You should join Uncle Yong

27
00:02:26,710 --> 00:02:28,310
in his home improvement business.

28
00:02:28,310 --> 00:02:29,190
No, no, no.

29
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:31,520
I prefer to be a street vendor
with Sis Bai.

30
00:02:33,590 --> 00:02:35,120
You paged each and every one of us

31
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:36,250
just to show us this?

32
00:02:36,310 --> 00:02:37,240
Of course.

33
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:38,280
See, I've even prepared

34
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:39,360
drinks for you guys.

35
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:39,960
Look,

36
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:41,910
in this skyscraper-filled city
of Shengcheng,

37
00:02:41,910 --> 00:02:42,680
there is a small space

38
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:43,800
exclusive to us.

39
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:44,870
How very nice.

40
00:02:44,870 --> 00:02:45,680
I feel like the whole city

41
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:46,430
is mine now.

42
00:02:46,870 --> 00:02:48,870
I don't need to own the entire Shengcheng.

43
00:02:48,870 --> 00:02:50,360
All I hope for is to build a home here

44
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:51,490
as soon as possible.

45
00:02:53,150 --> 00:02:55,360
Neither am I asking for much.

46
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,470
I just want a store.

47
00:02:58,470 --> 00:02:59,590
All deities up there,

48
00:02:59,590 --> 00:03:01,710
bless me with a rented store.

49
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:03,030
What about you, Xiaolan?

50
00:03:03,030 --> 00:03:04,760
What do you want in Shengcheng?

51
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:06,550
Me?

52
00:03:07,250 --> 00:03:09,210
I want to run freely,

53
00:03:09,470 --> 00:03:10,400
lead a good life,

54
00:03:10,910 --> 00:03:11,710
and...

55
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,060
make a lot of money!

56
00:03:13,590 --> 00:03:14,390
That's right.

57
00:03:14,540 --> 00:03:16,210
Make a lot of money!

58
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,300
Make a lot of money!

59
00:03:17,470 --> 00:03:18,430
Lead a good life!

60
00:03:18,910 --> 00:03:20,030
-Come on.
-Come on.

61
00:03:20,150 --> 00:03:24,310
Lead a good life, and make a lot of money!

62
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:27,910
How about taking a full set of sizes

63
00:03:27,910 --> 00:03:28,400
for each color

64
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:29,800
of these three plaid shirts?

65
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:30,120
Sounds nice.

66
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:30,470
Deal?

67
00:03:30,560 --> 00:03:30,890
Deal.

68
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:32,400
This blue shirt,

69
00:03:32,630 --> 00:03:35,310
and these striped ones...

70
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:36,710
I'll give you a discount on them,

71
00:03:36,710 --> 00:03:37,280
alright?

72
00:03:37,590 --> 00:03:38,790
Take a few more pieces

73
00:03:38,870 --> 00:03:39,840
of Size S and Size M,

74
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:40,310
okay?

75
00:03:40,430 --> 00:03:42,160
T-These two sizes sell better.

76
00:03:42,310 --> 00:03:42,750
Okay.

77
00:03:43,030 --> 00:03:43,800
Alright. I'll take these.

78
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:44,750
The same address, right?

79
00:03:44,750 --> 00:03:45,570
I'll pack them up now.

80
00:03:45,570 --> 00:03:46,090
Okay.

81
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:47,180
Thanks. Take care!

82
00:03:47,310 --> 00:03:49,079
Sometimes at the back of my mind,
there's a worry

83
00:03:49,079 --> 00:03:50,630
about whether an opportunity

84
00:03:50,630 --> 00:03:52,360
or an accident will come first.

85
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:55,590
Ms. Xia!

86
00:03:58,430 --> 00:03:59,660
Why just look at me?

87
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:01,120
Look at the goods.

88
00:04:02,150 --> 00:04:03,030
Both merchandise

89
00:04:03,030 --> 00:04:05,430
and merchants need observing in business.

90
00:04:06,710 --> 00:04:07,190
Right.

91
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:09,400
Only qualified merchandise
and competent merchants

92
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:10,910
can make for long-lasting business.

93
00:04:10,910 --> 00:04:12,470
Don't you worry. My goods here

94
00:04:12,470 --> 00:04:13,590
are all for foreign trade.

95
00:04:13,590 --> 00:04:15,050
Their quality is assured.

96
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:17,019
As for me, the merchant...

97
00:04:17,829 --> 00:04:19,160
Promises are of no use.

98
00:04:19,269 --> 00:04:20,310
You'll know what I'm like

99
00:04:20,310 --> 00:04:21,570
when you get to know me.

100
00:04:24,190 --> 00:04:25,250
Take a look around.

101
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:30,430
Mr. Chen.

102
00:04:31,210 --> 00:04:33,120
Which countries do you usually go to

103
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,310
for foreign trade?

104
00:04:34,750 --> 00:04:36,610
Do they include the Soviet Union?

105
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:37,720
The Soviet Union...

106
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:38,580
Yes, I go there.

107
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:39,600
Besides that,

108
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:41,800
I'd also travel to many other places
like Europe

109
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:42,460
and the U.S.

110
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:44,630
If changes were

111
00:04:44,630 --> 00:04:45,920
to happen to the Soviet Union,

112
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:47,780
would your business be affected?

113
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:49,000
If there were changes,

114
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,930
my business would certainly be...

115
00:04:54,190 --> 00:04:55,790
Changes in the Soviet Union?

116
00:04:56,220 --> 00:04:57,820
What changes could there be?

117
00:04:59,190 --> 00:05:01,000
He has no idea of that big historic event.

118
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,530
He can't be a time traveler.

119
00:05:03,490 --> 00:05:05,310
Whether its economy gets better or worse,

120
00:05:05,310 --> 00:05:06,970
there will be impacts, right?

121
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,060
You mean that, huh?

122
00:05:09,430 --> 00:05:10,030
It's true.

123
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:11,410
But don't worry.

124
00:05:11,650 --> 00:05:12,730
I'm a businessman

125
00:05:12,830 --> 00:05:13,630
of integrity.

126
00:05:13,830 --> 00:05:15,480
Whatever changes there may be
in that region,

127
00:05:15,480 --> 00:05:16,450
there's no way I will expose

128
00:05:16,450 --> 00:05:18,580
my customers to any negative effects.

129
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:20,510
Thank you then, Mr. Chen.

130
00:05:20,510 --> 00:05:21,170
No problem.

131
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:23,870
Does this polo shirt

132
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,200
come in other colors?

133
00:05:25,220 --> 00:05:25,700
Yes.

134
00:05:26,750 --> 00:05:27,510
Wait a moment.

135
00:05:27,510 --> 00:05:28,090
I'll get them for you.

136
00:05:28,090 --> 00:05:28,440
Okay.

137
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:31,170
Check out other items, if you will.

138
00:05:57,830 --> 00:05:58,360
Hold on.

139
00:05:58,920 --> 00:05:59,560
Granny Yu.

140
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:02,120
The rent you gave me yesterday...

141
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:03,430
I mean this ten-yuan bill.

142
00:06:03,430 --> 00:06:04,430
It's too worn out.

143
00:06:04,720 --> 00:06:05,920
I'd like a better one.

144
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:07,150
Not a problem.

145
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:12,160
Sorry about that.

146
00:06:13,190 --> 00:06:14,950
Is this one okay?

147
00:06:17,830 --> 00:06:19,070
I'm leaving then.

148
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:25,680
Alright, thanks.

149
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:48,240
Check it out.

150
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:49,300
Not one is missing.

151
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:50,480
I'll send them to the same

152
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:51,480
old address, okay?

153
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:51,830
Okay.

154
00:06:52,220 --> 00:06:54,420
The package will be out this afternoon.

155
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:55,960
Oh, right!

156
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:57,630
Next time when you come,

157
00:06:57,630 --> 00:06:58,510
you won't have to walk all the way in.

158
00:06:58,510 --> 00:07:00,830
I'm planning to move to that stall

159
00:07:00,950 --> 00:07:02,270
right by the entrance.

160
00:07:03,870 --> 00:07:05,190
Are you moving to a larger stall

161
00:07:05,190 --> 00:07:07,000
because you've made big money, Mr. Chen?

162
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:07,950
I wouldn't put it that way.

163
00:07:07,950 --> 00:07:08,950
I'm still counting on you

164
00:07:08,950 --> 00:07:10,770
and other patrons to support my business.

165
00:07:10,770 --> 00:07:11,480
This is the main reason

166
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:12,540
for the move, look.

167
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,310
I have a batch of trench coats

168
00:07:15,310 --> 00:07:16,370
piling up in stock.

169
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:17,740
If I don't put in some effort

170
00:07:17,740 --> 00:07:18,360
and sell them off

171
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:19,510
this autumn, I'll have trouble

172
00:07:19,510 --> 00:07:21,390
replenishing supplies next time.

173
00:07:21,390 --> 00:07:22,360
That's why I'm planning

174
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:24,040
to move to that stall by the entrance

175
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:25,300
for more foot traffic.

176
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:26,510
This trench coat of yours

177
00:07:26,510 --> 00:07:28,310
is nice both in style and fabric.

178
00:07:28,830 --> 00:07:30,430
But the design is too ahead of time,

179
00:07:30,430 --> 00:07:31,510
and the price is too high.

180
00:07:31,510 --> 00:07:32,750
No customers would opt for it.

181
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:33,630
They're afraid that if they buy any,

182
00:07:33,630 --> 00:07:35,159
they'll end up stuck with them
without a sale.

183
00:07:35,159 --> 00:07:36,190
Moving to a new stall

184
00:07:36,190 --> 00:07:37,990
won't help you sell these coats.

185
00:07:39,510 --> 00:07:41,020
Is there a string you can pull?

186
00:07:41,020 --> 00:07:41,920
Don't deny it.

187
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:43,000
Given what you said,

188
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,659
I'm sure you can pull a string.

189
00:07:45,390 --> 00:07:46,390
It's not a string.

190
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:47,690
But I do have an idea.

191
00:07:48,159 --> 00:07:48,870
What idea?

192
00:07:49,390 --> 00:07:51,250
Go ask some magazine publishers.

193
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:53,390
If these coat can get on a magazine,

194
00:07:53,390 --> 00:07:55,390
there won't be worries about sales.

195
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:57,480
Advertisements.

196
00:07:57,750 --> 00:07:59,810
Are you suggesting I advertise them?

197
00:07:59,870 --> 00:08:00,920
Yes, sort of.

198
00:08:01,340 --> 00:08:02,540
Something like that.

199
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:04,280
I mean apparel sponsorship.

200
00:08:06,390 --> 00:08:07,160
Ms. Xia...

201
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:08,390
No.

202
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:09,620
Respected Ms. Xia,

203
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:10,270
look,

204
00:08:10,510 --> 00:08:11,830
tomorrow, I'll do as you say.

205
00:08:11,830 --> 00:08:13,560
If it works out, you'll receive

206
00:08:13,870 --> 00:08:15,130
a share of the profits.

207
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:16,800
No need for that.

208
00:08:16,950 --> 00:08:17,390
I'm leaving.

209
00:08:17,390 --> 00:08:17,720
Okay.

210
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:18,520
Take care.

211
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:23,800
Mom!

212
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:26,920
Mom, I'm back!

213
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:29,800
Stop shouting.

214
00:08:30,950 --> 00:08:32,039
Remember the rules?

215
00:08:32,039 --> 00:08:33,280
Sorry, Granny Yu.

216
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:34,559
I didn't see you here.

217
00:08:34,750 --> 00:08:35,440
I promise

218
00:08:35,549 --> 00:08:37,210
I won't shout like that again.

219
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:39,370
Oh right, Granny Yu,

220
00:08:39,510 --> 00:08:40,720
last time, I noticed your blouse

221
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:42,120
was torn by a tree branch.

222
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:43,650
So I brought a new one for you

223
00:08:43,650 --> 00:08:44,840
from my procurement trip to Longcheng.

224
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:45,510
Take a look.

225
00:08:55,030 --> 00:08:57,480
I didn't ask you to buy me a new blouse.

226
00:08:58,670 --> 00:08:59,480
I was just...

227
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:01,080
planning to spend

228
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:03,520
ten yuan buying a new one.

229
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:06,570
If you think it's a loss for you,

230
00:09:06,870 --> 00:09:08,400
then take this blouse back.

231
00:09:09,480 --> 00:09:10,680
Thank you for the pay.

232
00:09:10,870 --> 00:09:11,820
Keep the blouse.

233
00:09:12,510 --> 00:09:14,710
I'll leave you to it and go upstairs now.

234
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:18,860
Your mother...

235
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:21,960
was picked up by a car.

236
00:09:22,870 --> 00:09:25,910
A car? Could it be Mr. Tang?

237
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,120
I'm back.

238
00:09:27,390 --> 00:09:27,870
Mom.

239
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:29,460
You're back, Xiaolan?

240
00:09:33,910 --> 00:09:34,550
Granny Yu,

241
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,670
I made some steamed buns.

242
00:09:36,670 --> 00:09:38,270
These are for you. Have a try.

243
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:43,660
We're heading upstairs then.

244
00:10:13,150 --> 00:10:15,150
Mom, are you just back from Uncle's?

245
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:16,000
Well, I was helping out

246
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,320
at Mayor Tang's place.

247
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:19,960
Mayor Tang?

248
00:10:20,630 --> 00:10:21,200
Come on.

249
00:10:21,790 --> 00:10:23,520
Eat the buns while they're hot.

250
00:10:25,130 --> 00:10:27,390
Mayor Tang's stomach problem persists,

251
00:10:27,670 --> 00:10:28,960
and nobody can cook for him at home.

252
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:30,080
His driver, Wang,

253
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:31,480
asked if I could help.

254
00:10:31,870 --> 00:10:34,200
So I went
and made him some millet porridge

255
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:35,360
and steamed buns

256
00:10:35,550 --> 00:10:37,210
that he can have as breakfast.

257
00:10:38,220 --> 00:10:38,820
Actually,

258
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:40,600
life hasn't been easy for Mayor Tang.

259
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:42,000
He was divorced long ago.

260
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:44,760
His children and ex-wife
are now in the U.S.

261
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:45,910
He has to cook

262
00:10:45,910 --> 00:10:46,750
for himself.

263
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:49,030
He often skips meals when he gets busy.

264
00:10:49,030 --> 00:10:50,960
That's how he got stomach trouble.

265
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:53,510
Did you hear all this

266
00:10:53,510 --> 00:10:54,440
from Mayor Tang?

267
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:56,040
No, Wang told me that.

268
00:10:56,510 --> 00:10:57,510
Mayor wasn't home

269
00:10:57,510 --> 00:10:58,680
when I was cooking there.

270
00:10:58,680 --> 00:10:59,720
I came back as soon as it finished

271
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,050
and didn't wait for him.

272
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:06,870
Was it appropriate for me to do that?

273
00:11:06,870 --> 00:11:08,400
I did nothing wrong, right?

274
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:09,630
Right.

275
00:11:10,150 --> 00:11:11,360
You were there to help out.

276
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:12,820
You got to do as you saw fit.

277
00:11:14,910 --> 00:11:15,440
Mom,

278
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,130
what do you think

279
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:18,630
of Mayor Tang?

280
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:22,080
I've only met him a few times.

281
00:11:22,740 --> 00:11:24,270
He seems amicable, though.

282
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:25,550
Plus...

283
00:11:25,730 --> 00:11:27,060
he's quite polite to me.

284
00:11:27,110 --> 00:11:29,240
Every time, he'd say he owes me thanks.

285
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:30,550
What else?

286
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:31,600
Else?

287
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:34,440
If he were not the mayor,

288
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:36,250
what would you think of him?

289
00:11:37,170 --> 00:11:38,600
What do you mean,
"if he were not the mayor"?

290
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:40,060
But he is in fact the mayor.

291
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:44,370
What are you even thinking?

292
00:11:44,870 --> 00:11:46,030
He's the mayor.

293
00:11:46,150 --> 00:11:47,680
I'm nowhere near his level.

294
00:11:48,360 --> 00:11:49,090
First of all,

295
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:51,250
I don't think that makes a difference.

296
00:11:51,250 --> 00:11:52,550
It doesn't matter if one is a mayor,
a farm worker,

297
00:11:52,550 --> 00:11:53,630
or a clothing vendor.

298
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:54,870
Those are just jobs.

299
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:56,000
Second,

300
00:11:56,530 --> 00:11:57,720
you're both divorced

301
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:58,440
and single.

302
00:11:58,740 --> 00:11:59,960
I think it's nice for you to get

303
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:01,420
to know each other better.

304
00:12:02,660 --> 00:12:04,320
You're getting ahead of yourself.

305
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:05,630
That is impossible.

306
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:08,080
He's the mayor, a big shot.

307
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:08,630
I don't even

308
00:12:08,630 --> 00:12:10,490
get to eat at the same table as him.

309
00:12:10,870 --> 00:12:12,270
If, several years ago,

310
00:12:12,420 --> 00:12:13,230
I had told you

311
00:12:13,410 --> 00:12:15,270
you could open clothing stores
in Jingcheng

312
00:12:15,270 --> 00:12:16,200
and Shengcheng,

313
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:18,410
would you have deemed it possible?

314
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:20,290
Comrade Liu Fen,

315
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:20,910
just do

316
00:12:20,910 --> 00:12:22,370
what your heart tells you.

317
00:12:22,550 --> 00:12:25,280
Try not to burden yourself
with so many concerns.

318
00:12:28,870 --> 00:12:29,930
Oh right, Xiaolan,

319
00:12:30,030 --> 00:12:32,080
your uncle said he'd drop by tomorrow

320
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:32,960
to talk to you

321
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:34,090
about some project.

322
00:12:35,870 --> 00:12:37,080
It seems it is an opportunity

323
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:38,610
that comes knocking first.

324
00:12:42,670 --> 00:12:43,270
Cheng.

325
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:44,870
Still sticking around?

326
00:12:44,870 --> 00:12:45,870
I'm about to finish this.

327
00:12:45,870 --> 00:12:46,480
Hey,

328
00:12:46,510 --> 00:12:47,600
a few days ago, my wife sent me

329
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,000
some local specialties.

330
00:12:49,030 --> 00:12:49,890
They're tasty.

331
00:12:49,910 --> 00:12:50,510
Have a try.

332
00:12:51,440 --> 00:12:51,870
Thanks.

333
00:12:51,870 --> 00:12:52,530
No problem.

334
00:12:56,980 --> 00:12:57,710
It's so sour.

335
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:58,320
Good, huh?

336
00:12:58,720 --> 00:12:59,390
Keep them then.

337
00:12:59,390 --> 00:13:00,120
I'm leaving.

338
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:00,630
Thanks.

339
00:13:00,630 --> 00:13:01,630
Don't mention it.

340
00:13:05,790 --> 00:13:06,360
Cheng,

341
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:07,750
actually,

342
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,630
Mr. Wu just loves to bluff.

343
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:11,210
Some files, in fact,

344
00:13:11,320 --> 00:13:12,450
aren't that urgent.

345
00:13:14,150 --> 00:13:15,600
Work has to be done sooner or later.

346
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:18,000
I'd like to finish it early
so I can go back to my girlfriend early.

347
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:19,660
You two are chummy lovebirds.

348
00:13:19,750 --> 00:13:20,630
When I become a lawyer,

349
00:13:20,630 --> 00:13:21,960
I'll have my wife move here too.

350
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:22,670
Alright, I'll leave you to it.

351
00:13:22,670 --> 00:13:23,360
I'm taking off.

352
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:23,670
Take care.

353
00:13:23,670 --> 00:13:24,080
Bye.

354
00:13:38,870 --> 00:13:40,080
My last home improvement client

355
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:40,880
was a big boss.

356
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:43,030
He thought I did my job fairly well.

357
00:13:43,030 --> 00:13:43,790
He reckoned me doing

358
00:13:43,790 --> 00:13:44,870
home improvement projects only

359
00:13:44,870 --> 00:13:45,930
was a bit of a waste,

360
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,400
and that I should dabble in
something else.

361
00:13:49,090 --> 00:13:49,880
Xiaolan,

362
00:13:49,910 --> 00:13:52,000
tell me, what is "bidding"?

363
00:13:52,550 --> 00:13:53,550
Simply put,

364
00:13:53,550 --> 00:13:55,240
clients requiring renovation services

365
00:13:55,240 --> 00:13:56,370
tend to shop around.

366
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:58,030
Bidding means

367
00:13:58,030 --> 00:13:59,200
that as the service provider,

368
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:00,360
we need to offer samples

369
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:02,140
for clients to make comparisons.

370
00:14:02,140 --> 00:14:02,960
Is that why you asked me

371
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:04,390
to take photos of the houses

372
00:14:04,390 --> 00:14:05,790
I renovated previously?

373
00:14:05,910 --> 00:14:06,270
Yes.

374
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:07,670
You're truly smart, Uncle.

375
00:14:07,670 --> 00:14:09,720
But that's just part of the materials
to be submitted.

376
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:11,080
Besides the company's credentials

377
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:12,200
and previous works,

378
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:14,000
we also need to prepare a tender document

379
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,200
and some design proposals

380
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,800
based on the client's needs.

381
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:18,270
I can see that this plan

382
00:14:18,270 --> 00:14:19,270
is written in great detail.

383
00:14:19,270 --> 00:14:20,550
It points out
what the tender should include,

384
00:14:20,550 --> 00:14:22,120
so it won't be hard for us to prepare one.

385
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:23,200
The problem is that we need to

386
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:24,930
decide which project to bid on.

387
00:14:25,030 --> 00:14:26,360
We have choices on that?

388
00:14:26,550 --> 00:14:27,080
Yes.

389
00:14:27,430 --> 00:14:29,300
This time, the renovation of Shengcheng

390
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:29,810
Guesthouse

391
00:14:29,810 --> 00:14:31,720
has been split
into several smaller projects.

392
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:32,630
I guess the purpose is to present

393
00:14:32,630 --> 00:14:34,320
opportunities
to privately owned enterprises.

394
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:35,630
Otherwise, establishments like Yuanhui,

395
00:14:35,630 --> 00:14:36,390
which used to focus on

396
00:14:36,390 --> 00:14:38,190
home improvement business only

397
00:14:38,270 --> 00:14:40,150
and haven't engaged
in a single government project,

398
00:14:40,150 --> 00:14:41,630
would probably never stand a chance

399
00:14:41,630 --> 00:14:43,290
of participating in this bid.

400
00:14:44,030 --> 00:14:45,390
Then this is an important matter.

401
00:14:45,390 --> 00:14:45,850
Well...

402
00:14:46,750 --> 00:14:48,210
are we able to handle this?

403
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:49,390
Uncle, don't worry.

404
00:14:49,390 --> 00:14:50,390
I'll be there for you.

405
00:14:50,390 --> 00:14:52,450
Then what about your clothing store?

406
00:14:52,510 --> 00:14:54,320
All is fine. It won't be affected.

407
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:56,030
Even if we only win
a bid for a tiny project

408
00:14:56,030 --> 00:14:57,120
this time,

409
00:14:57,240 --> 00:14:58,150
we'll still make our way

410
00:14:58,150 --> 00:15:00,410
to the renovation market in Shengcheng.

411
00:15:01,410 --> 00:15:02,720
This seems to be a good opportunity

412
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:03,790
for Yuanhui.

413
00:15:05,030 --> 00:15:07,270
An opportunity for me, too.

414
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:08,800
By the way,

415
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:10,150
two other bidders are

416
00:15:10,150 --> 00:15:10,950
a state-owned

417
00:15:11,150 --> 00:15:11,840
enterprise

418
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:14,260
and a venture backed by Gangdao capital.

419
00:15:14,390 --> 00:15:16,790
The name of that Gangdao company is...

420
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:19,600
"Chengrong Tianchen."

421
00:15:20,080 --> 00:15:21,750
You mean Chengrong Group
owned by Du Chengrong

422
00:15:21,750 --> 00:15:22,680
from Gangdao?

423
00:15:22,790 --> 00:15:23,870
Yes, yes,

424
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:24,530
exactly.

425
00:15:32,150 --> 00:15:33,080
Well, Uncle,

426
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:35,550
it's about time

427
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:36,480
I got off work

428
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:38,000
and went on a date.

429
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:40,320
I'll get going then.

430
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:40,840
Bye bye.

431
00:15:42,320 --> 00:15:43,000
Granny Yu,

432
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:43,750
bye bye.

433
00:15:45,630 --> 00:15:47,600
When young people are in love...

434
00:15:48,750 --> 00:15:49,810
Y-Young people...

435
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:51,360
I don't live here.

436
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:52,150
I've rented a place.

437
00:15:52,150 --> 00:15:53,080
I'm leaving now.

438
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:07,580
Come on.

439
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:13,720
[Time is money; Efficiency is life]

440
00:16:13,150 --> 00:16:14,200
Wide open views.

441
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:16,320
Everything's within a glance.

442
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:17,200
How did you find this place?

443
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:19,260
I'm Xia Xiaolan. Give me some credit.

444
00:16:20,960 --> 00:16:21,720
Look.

445
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:24,510
Shengcheng is really huge.

446
00:16:25,060 --> 00:16:26,570
Seeing from your home,

447
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:27,760
it's a sea of lights.

448
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:30,000
Seeing from here,

449
00:16:30,030 --> 00:16:32,290
there are bustling commercial streets.

450
00:16:32,470 --> 00:16:33,670
At Shengcheng's pace of development,

451
00:16:33,670 --> 00:16:34,840
it shouldn't be long

452
00:16:35,150 --> 00:16:36,000
before the side across

453
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:37,600
is filled with skyscrapers.

454
00:16:37,960 --> 00:16:39,440
By then, your real estate agency

455
00:16:39,440 --> 00:16:40,840
can be set up in this area.

456
00:16:40,910 --> 00:16:42,080
Right now, all I want is to

457
00:16:42,080 --> 00:16:43,670
quickly launch my clothing store

458
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:45,330
and accumulate capital fast.

459
00:16:47,520 --> 00:16:48,450
It would be great

460
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:50,010
if I could open my shop here.

461
00:16:50,150 --> 00:16:51,480
Surrounded by streets in three sides,

462
00:16:51,480 --> 00:16:52,670
it can be seen

463
00:16:52,910 --> 00:16:54,150
from all intersections.

464
00:16:54,150 --> 00:16:55,840
It will definitely be
the most eye-catching

465
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:57,770
presence in this entire district.

466
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:02,320
Look.

467
00:17:02,910 --> 00:17:04,369
That spot with no lights on

468
00:17:04,750 --> 00:17:06,349
probably hasn't been taken yet.

469
00:17:06,349 --> 00:17:07,550
Maybe it's still for rent.

470
00:17:07,550 --> 00:17:08,750
Shall we check it out tomorrow?

471
00:17:08,750 --> 00:17:09,200
Okay.

472
00:17:09,349 --> 00:17:10,000
Right there?

473
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,000
Yes, right there.

474
00:17:18,680 --> 00:17:19,210
Morning.

475
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:19,720
Morning.

476
00:17:19,720 --> 00:17:20,650
Morning, Cheng.

477
00:17:23,829 --> 00:17:24,890
New environments.

478
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:26,270
New careers.

479
00:17:26,750 --> 00:17:27,680
New challenges.

480
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:30,340
We are all trying hard to adapt

481
00:17:30,680 --> 00:17:31,740
and doing our best.

482
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:35,110
Careful!

483
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:36,640
Quick.

484
00:17:36,920 --> 00:17:38,200
Work overtime if we have to!

485
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:38,720
Yes.

486
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:54,680
Xiaolan,

487
00:17:55,790 --> 00:17:56,720
it's time to eat.

488
00:17:56,790 --> 00:17:57,720
Okay, coming.

489
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:09,880
Granny Yu,

490
00:18:10,070 --> 00:18:10,920
you're back.

491
00:18:11,590 --> 00:18:13,680
Have you eaten yet? I made dumplings.

492
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:18,400
Nobody in this world

493
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:19,810
can be more kind-hearted and nicer

494
00:18:19,810 --> 00:18:21,660
than you, Comrade Liu Fen.

495
00:18:32,700 --> 00:18:35,190
[From Chen Xiliang: Give me a call soon]

496
00:18:39,640 --> 00:18:41,070
You seem to be enjoying this.

497
00:18:41,070 --> 00:18:41,920
Well, any deals

498
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,450
with magazine publishers?

499
00:18:45,590 --> 00:18:46,520
Yes, I nailed it.

500
00:18:47,050 --> 00:18:48,720
For a magazine's issue
for the second half of this month,

501
00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:51,120
the actor Zhou Wangjing
will wear my coats.

502
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:56,490
Then why are you still
pulling a long face?

503
00:18:56,800 --> 00:18:58,110
I went to great lengths to finally

504
00:18:58,110 --> 00:18:59,570
connect to Zhou Wangjing.

505
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:00,750
I was being toyed with

506
00:19:00,750 --> 00:19:02,410
by a bunch of magazine editors

507
00:19:02,510 --> 00:19:03,310
all last week.

508
00:19:03,640 --> 00:19:04,680
We'll talk about this later.

509
00:19:03,940 --> 00:19:08,120
[Jingcheng Friend for Fashion Magazine]

510
00:19:04,680 --> 00:19:05,030
Sure.

511
00:19:05,070 --> 00:19:06,270
Shall we have dinner together?

512
00:19:06,270 --> 00:19:06,680
Okay.

513
00:19:06,780 --> 00:19:07,310
Let's go.

514
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:08,640
Join us then, all of you.

515
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:09,160
Sure.

516
00:19:09,790 --> 00:19:11,190
Ms. Xia, you have no idea.

517
00:19:11,510 --> 00:19:13,310
Those editors drank lots of wine

518
00:19:13,640 --> 00:19:15,480
and accepted all the presents I gave them.

519
00:19:15,480 --> 00:19:17,160
But when it came to bringing my coats
to the cover,

520
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:18,030
they started making excuses.

521
00:19:18,030 --> 00:19:18,960
Take it, please.

522
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:20,410
Here you are.

523
00:19:20,520 --> 00:19:21,350
L-Let me see you out.

524
00:19:21,350 --> 00:19:22,880
No need. Don't stand on ceremony.

525
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:23,680
Alright then.

526
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:25,160
Take care, everyone.

527
00:19:25,160 --> 00:19:25,790
Editor-in-Chief.

528
00:19:25,790 --> 00:19:26,270
Okay.

529
00:19:26,270 --> 00:19:26,790
Mr. Chen.

530
00:19:26,790 --> 00:19:27,270
Hey, Mr. Wang.

531
00:19:27,270 --> 00:19:27,830
Just wait to hear from us.

532
00:19:27,830 --> 00:19:28,550
Take care.

533
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:29,680
Thank you so much!

534
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:30,110
No problem.

535
00:19:30,110 --> 00:19:31,070
Come visit Shengcheng when available!

536
00:19:31,070 --> 00:19:31,830
Sure, sure.

537
00:19:34,030 --> 00:19:35,440
Later, enlightened by a kind soul,

538
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:36,640
I realized the truth.

539
00:19:37,040 --> 00:19:38,590
Those editors looked down on me for being

540
00:19:38,590 --> 00:19:39,790
a self-employed stall vendor.

541
00:19:39,790 --> 00:19:40,720
Though I offered to sponsor them

542
00:19:40,720 --> 00:19:42,350
with free apparel
for the magazine's photoshoots,

543
00:19:42,350 --> 00:19:44,480
they still turned their noses up at it.

544
00:19:45,830 --> 00:19:46,640
Have you eaten yet?

545
00:19:46,640 --> 00:19:47,550
Care for some noodles?

546
00:19:47,550 --> 00:19:48,680
No need. I've eaten.

547
00:19:48,790 --> 00:19:49,450
Herbal tea?

548
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:50,400
Okay.

549
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:51,400
Sir,

550
00:19:51,550 --> 00:19:52,260
two cups of herbal tea.

551
00:19:52,260 --> 00:19:53,190
Okay, just a sec.

552
00:19:54,070 --> 00:19:54,680
Ms. Xia,

553
00:19:55,350 --> 00:19:56,460
don't you think those

554
00:19:56,460 --> 00:19:58,320
men's coats I designed look nice?

555
00:19:58,750 --> 00:20:00,280
Aren't the fabric and style

556
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:01,440
high-class enough?

557
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:02,790
I think they're perfect.

558
00:20:02,790 --> 00:20:03,590
The editors rejected me

559
00:20:03,590 --> 00:20:05,400
because I don't own a brand, right?

560
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:06,680
That aside,

561
00:20:07,030 --> 00:20:08,560
what else do I fall short of?

562
00:20:09,510 --> 00:20:10,640
As you just said,

563
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:12,720
the only thing you lack is a brand.

564
00:20:12,720 --> 00:20:13,350
If you have

565
00:20:13,370 --> 00:20:14,440
your own brand

566
00:20:14,550 --> 00:20:16,440
and hire actors to shoot commercials

567
00:20:16,440 --> 00:20:18,240
for the clothes designed by you—

568
00:20:18,350 --> 00:20:19,680
like the ones on TV,

569
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:20,720
you won't have to beg...

570
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:21,830
Have my own brand?

571
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:27,420
I've been thinking about the same thing.

572
00:20:28,590 --> 00:20:29,310
Ms. Xia,

573
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:30,740
respected Ms. Xia,

574
00:20:30,830 --> 00:20:31,960
I knew the two of us

575
00:20:31,960 --> 00:20:33,760
would come up with the same idea.

576
00:20:34,750 --> 00:20:36,010
Again, I said too much.

577
00:20:36,240 --> 00:20:37,510
Actually, on my way here,

578
00:20:37,510 --> 00:20:39,200
I was contemplating it the entire time.

579
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:40,240
I think the two of us

580
00:20:40,240 --> 00:20:42,100
can partner up and create a brand.

581
00:20:42,510 --> 00:20:43,270
We can hire actors

582
00:20:43,270 --> 00:20:44,740
to shoot commercials like you said.

583
00:20:44,740 --> 00:20:45,870
I believe, that way,

584
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:47,610
we can make a name for our brand.

585
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:50,060
In the timeline where I came from,

586
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:52,960
it'd take Chen Xiliang a few more years

587
00:20:53,250 --> 00:20:54,200
to officially launch

588
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:55,960
"Luna," the brand that brought him wealth.

589
00:20:55,960 --> 00:20:57,920
Now, it's going to happen ahead of time.

590
00:20:57,920 --> 00:20:58,480
I'm not sure

591
00:20:58,480 --> 00:21:00,030
what changes this will trigger.

592
00:21:00,030 --> 00:21:00,680
Ms. Xia.

593
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:02,160
Dear Ms. Xia.

594
00:21:02,880 --> 00:21:03,960
My dearest Ms. Xia,

595
00:21:04,640 --> 00:21:06,370
please do give it some thought.

596
00:21:06,880 --> 00:21:08,410
Let's partner up, shall we?

597
00:21:10,310 --> 00:21:12,490
Perhaps this is a foreshadowing of fate.

598
00:21:12,490 --> 00:21:13,110
I don't know

599
00:21:13,110 --> 00:21:15,070
what kind of story that my encounter

600
00:21:15,070 --> 00:21:16,730
with Chen Xiliang will begin.

601
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:19,270
Dear Ms. Xia,

602
00:21:19,680 --> 00:21:21,540
I'm not suggesting it on impulse.

603
00:21:21,640 --> 00:21:24,000
I have to earn my money hard
from wholesale.

604
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:25,440
I'm not content with that.

605
00:21:25,440 --> 00:21:27,000
People would sneeze at me if I offered

606
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:28,240
to alter their garments.

607
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:29,550
I also think that's beneath me.

608
00:21:29,550 --> 00:21:31,030
Creating a brand is a path

609
00:21:31,030 --> 00:21:31,920
taken by few.

610
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:33,510
Others don't have the guts,

611
00:21:33,510 --> 00:21:34,200
but I do.

612
00:21:34,680 --> 00:21:35,540
I'd like to try.

613
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:37,640
It is indeed

614
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:39,240
a good idea to create a brand.

615
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:40,590
That said, you're an expert

616
00:21:40,590 --> 00:21:41,680
at tailoring and designs,

617
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:43,750
and your family has connections
with garment factories.

618
00:21:43,750 --> 00:21:45,210
Why partner with me at all?

619
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:47,310
Because you have a knack for sales.

620
00:21:47,310 --> 00:21:48,160
I understand.

621
00:21:48,750 --> 00:21:50,280
Nice clothes are just rags

622
00:21:50,310 --> 00:21:51,370
if they can't sell.

623
00:21:51,860 --> 00:21:53,830
I couldn't have fathomed
what you thought of—

624
00:21:53,830 --> 00:21:55,030
an ad campaign through a magazine.

625
00:21:55,030 --> 00:21:56,160
You have what I need.

626
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:05,550
Although

627
00:22:06,110 --> 00:22:07,750
we've only met a few times,

628
00:22:08,150 --> 00:22:09,280
I can feel...

629
00:22:09,310 --> 00:22:11,270
that you're different from everyone else.

630
00:22:11,270 --> 00:22:12,510
It's just like...

631
00:22:13,960 --> 00:22:14,640
like...

632
00:22:15,550 --> 00:22:17,950
you popped up from nowhere
to come to my aid.

633
00:22:18,070 --> 00:22:20,070
You're like a gift from heaven to me.

634
00:22:21,270 --> 00:22:22,960
As long as you agree to work with me,

635
00:22:22,960 --> 00:22:24,160
I'll say yes to any...

636
00:22:26,550 --> 00:22:29,550
I mean, I'll really consider
any conditions you make.

637
00:22:30,270 --> 00:22:31,110
I know

638
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:32,750
there have to be certain rules

639
00:22:32,750 --> 00:22:34,680
when we become business partners.

640
00:22:35,380 --> 00:22:36,270
But don't you worry.

641
00:22:36,270 --> 00:22:38,930
I'll definitely not
put you in a difficult spot.

642
00:22:39,750 --> 00:22:40,480
Mr. Chen,

643
00:22:41,030 --> 00:22:42,230
if you had just said

644
00:22:42,260 --> 00:22:43,640
you'd say yes to any conditions I made,

645
00:22:43,640 --> 00:22:45,840
I would've stood up and left right away.

646
00:22:46,110 --> 00:22:48,510
I bit my tongue at the last moment,
didn't I?

647
00:22:49,110 --> 00:22:51,590
Right now, I do need

648
00:22:51,590 --> 00:22:52,920
a profitable business.

649
00:22:53,920 --> 00:22:55,180
You and your brand have

650
00:22:55,640 --> 00:22:57,100
great potential, indeed.

651
00:22:57,780 --> 00:22:58,920
When it comes to garment making,

652
00:22:58,920 --> 00:23:01,120
you truly have more resources than I do.

653
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:02,550
I can handle marketing,

654
00:23:02,550 --> 00:23:03,480
but you'll have to run

655
00:23:03,480 --> 00:23:05,610
the day-to-day operations yourself.

656
00:23:08,160 --> 00:23:09,020
How about this?

657
00:23:09,720 --> 00:23:12,160
I'll take 45% of the shares,

658
00:23:12,480 --> 00:23:13,310
and you 55%.

659
00:23:14,030 --> 00:23:15,000
What do you think?

660
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:15,550
I agree.

661
00:23:16,230 --> 00:23:16,790
Look,

662
00:23:17,030 --> 00:23:19,160
I'll draft a contract as soon as possible.

663
00:23:19,160 --> 00:23:19,880
We can discuss

664
00:23:19,880 --> 00:23:20,940
the details later.

665
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:23,040
Your boyfriend Zhou is a paralegal.

666
00:23:23,040 --> 00:23:24,110
I will definitely not

667
00:23:24,110 --> 00:23:25,070
play any tricks in the contract.

668
00:23:25,070 --> 00:23:26,670
You can rest assured of that.

669
00:23:27,030 --> 00:23:28,240
Let's make it a great cause,

670
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:29,970
now that we're committed to it.

671
00:23:30,350 --> 00:23:31,830
Our current goal is to open branches

672
00:23:31,830 --> 00:23:33,270
in all major cities across the country

673
00:23:33,270 --> 00:23:34,400
within one year.

674
00:23:35,070 --> 00:23:37,530
Where would you like
to place our first shop?

675
00:23:37,890 --> 00:23:39,710
I can get hold of many resources
in Longcheng,

676
00:23:39,710 --> 00:23:40,640
and I'm familiar with that city.

677
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:42,270
It won't be hard to open a shop there.

678
00:23:42,270 --> 00:23:44,670
Given Shengcheng's proximity to Gangdao,

679
00:23:45,240 --> 00:23:47,370
I think we should have a shop there too.

680
00:23:47,880 --> 00:23:49,400
We're opening shops anyway. How about

681
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:50,660
we open two at one time?

682
00:23:53,550 --> 00:23:54,610
One in Shengcheng.

683
00:23:54,750 --> 00:23:55,750
Two in Longcheng.

684
00:23:55,880 --> 00:23:56,830
What do you think?

685
00:23:56,830 --> 00:23:58,350
We'll open three shops on the same day

686
00:23:58,350 --> 00:23:59,480
to make a big splash.

687
00:23:59,680 --> 00:24:00,380
Sounds good.

688
00:24:00,380 --> 00:24:02,310
Let's open three shops all at once.

689
00:24:02,640 --> 00:24:04,240
I've been to Gangdao before.

690
00:24:04,510 --> 00:24:06,310
The shops there all use English.

691
00:24:06,510 --> 00:24:08,240
They look fancy and stylish

692
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:09,070
to me.

693
00:24:09,440 --> 00:24:10,720
You've been to college.

694
00:24:10,720 --> 00:24:11,980
I'm sure you know a lot.

695
00:24:12,270 --> 00:24:14,160
Why don't you give a name to our brand?

696
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:15,200
No, this is your own brand.

697
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:16,800
You should name it yourself.

698
00:24:16,920 --> 00:24:18,450
I can offer you some advice.

699
00:24:19,240 --> 00:24:20,070
I'll buy an English dictionary

700
00:24:20,070 --> 00:24:22,000
and flip through it for ideas then.

701
00:24:22,570 --> 00:24:24,420
As for the shop in Shengcheng,

702
00:24:24,590 --> 00:24:25,480
I'll have to trouble you

703
00:24:25,480 --> 00:24:26,940
to help me pick a location.

704
00:24:27,750 --> 00:24:28,920
Shengcheng...

705
00:24:30,030 --> 00:24:31,690
There's actually a nice spot.

706
00:24:35,790 --> 00:24:36,520
Ms. Xia,

707
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:38,680
you really are my lifesaver.

708
00:24:38,920 --> 00:24:40,450
What a wonderful location.

709
00:24:40,450 --> 00:24:41,550
Whichever way people come from,

710
00:24:41,550 --> 00:24:43,080
they'll see our shop first.

711
00:24:47,270 --> 00:24:48,250
Wait, something's off.

712
00:24:48,250 --> 00:24:48,970
Why hasn't

713
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:50,960
this prime location been rented yet?

714
00:24:50,960 --> 00:24:52,760
I've inquired about this place.

715
00:24:53,240 --> 00:24:54,510
The ground floor is for shops,

716
00:24:54,510 --> 00:24:56,070
and the second for apartments.

717
00:24:56,070 --> 00:24:58,110
This property
partly belongs to a food factory,

718
00:24:58,110 --> 00:24:58,680
and partly

719
00:24:58,680 --> 00:24:59,680
to an individual.

720
00:24:59,920 --> 00:25:02,310
That person is said to be
very difficult to deal with.

721
00:25:02,310 --> 00:25:04,030
So the food factory would rather

722
00:25:04,030 --> 00:25:05,200
leave this building vacant

723
00:25:05,200 --> 00:25:06,240
than bother to hold

724
00:25:06,240 --> 00:25:07,100
a negotiation.

725
00:25:07,310 --> 00:25:08,310
What a hassle.

726
00:25:10,110 --> 00:25:12,310
Success requires addressing trouble.

727
00:25:12,920 --> 00:25:13,800
Just go back to Longcheng

728
00:25:13,800 --> 00:25:15,400
and get the brand and trademark ready.

729
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:17,070
However hard it is to strike a lease deal,

730
00:25:17,070 --> 00:25:18,640
I'll make sure we secure this spot.

731
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:19,200
Okay.

732
00:25:22,980 --> 00:25:23,740
Granny Yu,

733
00:25:24,430 --> 00:25:26,440
I just learned how to make
stir-fried rice noodles with beef.

734
00:25:26,440 --> 00:25:27,420
I heard people here

735
00:25:27,420 --> 00:25:28,310
all enjoy this.

736
00:25:28,510 --> 00:25:30,440
Taste it and tell me what you think.

737
00:25:33,310 --> 00:25:33,830
Mom,

738
00:25:34,270 --> 00:25:36,530
that old lady hasn't warmed up to you yet?

739
00:25:37,310 --> 00:25:38,370
It won't take long.

740
00:25:41,830 --> 00:25:42,540
Let me help.

741
00:25:42,720 --> 00:25:44,000
Mind the stuff. Close the door.

742
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:44,270
Got it.

743
00:25:44,270 --> 00:25:45,010
Yong...

744
00:25:49,030 --> 00:25:51,070
Where did you get these many paintings?

745
00:25:51,070 --> 00:25:52,000
Xiaolan asked me

746
00:25:52,110 --> 00:25:53,820
to get her some oil paintings.

747
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:54,920
Tell me where you want them to be,

748
00:25:54,920 --> 00:25:55,960
and I'll hang them up later.

749
00:25:55,960 --> 00:25:57,220
Okay. Let's eat first.

750
00:25:59,070 --> 00:26:00,440
Stir-fried rice noodles with beef?

751
00:26:00,440 --> 00:26:00,970
Try some.

752
00:26:01,080 --> 00:26:01,830
Though I've been here

753
00:26:01,830 --> 00:26:02,720
for many years,

754
00:26:03,010 --> 00:26:03,930
I still think

755
00:26:03,960 --> 00:26:05,590
the braised noodles in our hometown
are the best.

756
00:26:05,590 --> 00:26:06,790
I'm not used to this stuff.

757
00:26:06,790 --> 00:26:08,000
Xiaolan, you try some.

758
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:08,640
I'll taste it then.

759
00:26:08,640 --> 00:26:10,570
Did I not make it the authentic way?

760
00:26:12,180 --> 00:26:13,710
You already did a great job.

761
00:26:14,270 --> 00:26:15,160
But people's taste in food

762
00:26:15,160 --> 00:26:16,490
doesn't change easily.

763
00:26:16,650 --> 00:26:17,280
I guess

764
00:26:17,310 --> 00:26:19,310
it'll taste better with some chili.

765
00:26:19,720 --> 00:26:20,780
Oh right, Xiaolan.

766
00:26:21,110 --> 00:26:22,970
I asked about that small building

767
00:26:23,030 --> 00:26:24,160
you have your eye on.

768
00:26:24,240 --> 00:26:25,400
The food factory finds it

769
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:26,110
too troublesome

770
00:26:26,110 --> 00:26:27,370
to hold a negotiation.

771
00:26:27,880 --> 00:26:28,920
Can they give us

772
00:26:28,920 --> 00:26:30,290
the other owner's information

773
00:26:30,290 --> 00:26:30,900
then?

774
00:26:31,160 --> 00:26:32,320
We'll talk to this person ourselves.

775
00:26:32,320 --> 00:26:33,440
When the three parties reach an agreement,

776
00:26:33,440 --> 00:26:35,540
all we will need to do is sit down
and sign a contract.

777
00:26:35,540 --> 00:26:36,340
Oh right, Mom.

778
00:26:36,800 --> 00:26:38,240
When the Shengcheng shop opens,

779
00:26:38,240 --> 00:26:39,510
you'll be the manager of it.

780
00:26:39,510 --> 00:26:41,080
Chen Xiliang has agreed to that.

781
00:26:41,080 --> 00:26:42,310
Well, Uncle, about that building,

782
00:26:42,310 --> 00:26:43,310
I'm afraid I'll have to trouble you

783
00:26:43,310 --> 00:26:44,110
to make inquiries again.

784
00:26:44,110 --> 00:26:44,510
No problem.

785
00:26:44,510 --> 00:26:45,440
I'm already scheduled to meet with someone

786
00:26:45,440 --> 00:26:46,240
and talk about it this afternoon.

787
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:46,590
Okay.

788
00:26:46,790 --> 00:26:47,640
Tell me where you'd like

789
00:26:47,640 --> 00:26:48,510
to place these oil paintings.

790
00:26:48,510 --> 00:26:50,400
I'll hang them up for you after lunch.

791
00:26:50,400 --> 00:26:51,080
No need for that.

792
00:26:51,080 --> 00:26:52,800
The paintings are for bidding

793
00:26:52,830 --> 00:26:54,360
on the guesthouse project.

794
00:26:54,680 --> 00:26:55,270
Xiaolan,

795
00:26:56,050 --> 00:26:57,350
are you giving them away as gifts?

796
00:26:57,350 --> 00:26:58,400
Isn't it inappropriate?

797
00:26:58,400 --> 00:26:59,400
Don't get me wrong.

798
00:26:59,400 --> 00:27:01,730
We'll compete based on our capabilities.

799
00:27:01,750 --> 00:27:03,240
But we need to show our advantages

800
00:27:03,240 --> 00:27:04,770
during the bidding, right?

801
00:27:05,680 --> 00:27:06,940
Let me check these out.

802
00:27:20,440 --> 00:27:20,970
Alright.

803
00:27:21,680 --> 00:27:22,400
This is the one.

804
00:27:22,150 --> 00:27:24,120
[Gong Yang, Art Academy]

805
00:27:30,400 --> 00:27:31,000
Xiaolan.

806
00:27:31,400 --> 00:27:32,920
I look smart in this, don't I?

807
00:27:32,920 --> 00:27:33,720
My little bag.

808
00:27:34,400 --> 00:27:35,590
Let me tuck it under my arm.

809
00:27:35,590 --> 00:27:36,520
Perfect, right?

810
00:27:36,720 --> 00:27:37,120
Right.

811
00:27:37,270 --> 00:27:39,870
You do look the part
of a private entrepreneur.

812
00:27:41,680 --> 00:27:43,340
That must be Gong Yang, right?

813
00:27:45,680 --> 00:27:46,280
Gong Yang!

814
00:27:47,660 --> 00:27:48,990
Hello, I'm Xia Xiaolan.

815
00:27:51,400 --> 00:27:53,200
This is Mr. Liu, the owner of Yuanhui.

816
00:27:53,200 --> 00:27:54,260
He's also my uncle.

817
00:27:54,450 --> 00:27:55,270
Today, you'll be with us

818
00:27:55,270 --> 00:27:56,160
for a tour first.

819
00:27:56,160 --> 00:27:57,240
Then I'll tell you

820
00:27:57,240 --> 00:27:58,640
our specific requirements.

821
00:27:58,640 --> 00:27:59,070
Okay.

822
00:27:59,550 --> 00:28:00,640
I have classes this afternoon.

823
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:02,170
How long will the tour take?

824
00:28:02,240 --> 00:28:02,970
Don't worry.

825
00:28:03,030 --> 00:28:05,290
We promise you won't be late for classes.

826
00:28:06,110 --> 00:28:07,400
If it isn't Xia Xiaolan,

827
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:08,350
Ms. Xia.

828
00:28:10,070 --> 00:28:11,510
Long time no see, Ms. Xia.

829
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:14,110
It turns out you're pursuing a career

830
00:28:14,110 --> 00:28:15,320
in the renovation industry.

831
00:28:15,320 --> 00:28:17,520
But I think a talented lady like you,

832
00:28:17,550 --> 00:28:18,480
Ms. Xia,

833
00:28:18,790 --> 00:28:20,070
should join a big corporation,

834
00:28:20,070 --> 00:28:22,270
a design institute, or something alike,

835
00:28:22,270 --> 00:28:23,690
even if you're not going to Gangdao.

836
00:28:23,690 --> 00:28:24,920
Why did you choose this company,

837
00:28:24,920 --> 00:28:26,440
which seems to be struggling?

838
00:28:26,440 --> 00:28:27,240
I wonder, Ms. Xia,

839
00:28:27,240 --> 00:28:28,440
if you have heard of a company

840
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:29,970
named Chengrong Tianchen.

841
00:28:30,110 --> 00:28:32,030
It invests generously in every project.

842
00:28:32,030 --> 00:28:32,880
You're exactly

843
00:28:32,880 --> 00:28:34,880
the kind of talent we need right now.

844
00:28:35,760 --> 00:28:36,650
Mr. Du,

845
00:28:37,240 --> 00:28:39,880
since this "struggling company" of ours

846
00:28:40,030 --> 00:28:41,590
can be a rival to that "generous company"

847
00:28:41,590 --> 00:28:42,400
of yours,

848
00:28:42,640 --> 00:28:43,240
it means

849
00:28:43,240 --> 00:28:44,970
ours has boundless prospects.

850
00:28:45,310 --> 00:28:46,720
I prefer to stay

851
00:28:47,070 --> 00:28:48,400
where there is a future.

852
00:28:50,510 --> 00:28:51,240
Fair enough.

853
00:28:51,730 --> 00:28:53,410
If we can

854
00:28:53,440 --> 00:28:54,830
cooperate this time,

855
00:28:55,420 --> 00:28:56,920
I'd love to have more exchanges

856
00:28:56,920 --> 00:28:58,000
with you, Ms. Xia.

857
00:28:58,960 --> 00:29:00,270
I don't think your mind

858
00:29:00,270 --> 00:29:01,880
is on the bidding at all, Mr. Du.

859
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:03,470
You and I have nothing to talk about.

860
00:29:03,470 --> 00:29:04,400
Let's go, Uncle.

861
00:29:08,030 --> 00:29:08,690
Sassy girl.

862
00:29:10,240 --> 00:29:11,170
The guesthouse

863
00:29:11,200 --> 00:29:13,110
has 67 rooms of various sizes,

864
00:29:13,480 --> 00:29:14,940
3 large conference rooms,

865
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:16,400
and 9 smaller ones.

866
00:29:16,830 --> 00:29:18,290
There are 2 dinning halls,

867
00:29:18,350 --> 00:29:19,920
and one reception lobby.

868
00:29:20,380 --> 00:29:21,050
These places all

869
00:29:21,050 --> 00:29:23,070
fall within the scope of this tender.

870
00:29:23,070 --> 00:29:24,550
You can bid for renovating them all,

871
00:29:24,550 --> 00:29:26,520
or just some of them.

872
00:29:26,930 --> 00:29:27,440
You can find

873
00:29:27,440 --> 00:29:28,610
all this information in our profile.

874
00:29:28,610 --> 00:29:29,350
Please refer to it

875
00:29:29,350 --> 00:29:30,640
for more details.

876
00:29:31,480 --> 00:29:33,160
Also, you can take on-site measurements

877
00:29:33,160 --> 00:29:34,440
if necessary.

878
00:29:34,750 --> 00:29:36,150
Can we take a look around?

879
00:29:36,310 --> 00:29:36,830
Sure.

880
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:38,130
I'll be in my office.

881
00:29:38,130 --> 00:29:39,510
Let me know if you need anything.

882
00:29:39,510 --> 00:29:39,920
Okay.

883
00:29:39,940 --> 00:29:40,940
Got it, thank you.

884
00:29:40,960 --> 00:29:41,590
Thanks!

885
00:29:42,240 --> 00:29:43,400
Uncle, shall we check out

886
00:29:43,400 --> 00:29:44,240
the dining halls downstairs?

887
00:29:44,240 --> 00:29:45,100
Sure, let's go.

888
00:29:48,720 --> 00:29:49,270
Mr. Du.

889
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:50,480
Ms. Xia,

890
00:29:50,550 --> 00:29:51,640
what can I do for you?

891
00:29:51,640 --> 00:29:53,570
We are competitors now, aren't we?

892
00:29:53,750 --> 00:29:55,070
Why are you following me?

893
00:29:55,070 --> 00:29:56,800
Aren't your people over there?

894
00:29:56,920 --> 00:29:58,000
Good thing that we're competitors.

895
00:29:58,000 --> 00:29:59,000
We can cooperate.

896
00:29:59,920 --> 00:30:01,030
Cooperate with a seemingly

897
00:30:01,030 --> 00:30:02,890
"struggling company" like ours?

898
00:30:03,550 --> 00:30:04,590
Of course.

899
00:30:11,590 --> 00:30:12,130
Xiaolan,

900
00:30:12,160 --> 00:30:13,000
look at this place.

901
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:13,750
How very nice.

902
00:30:13,750 --> 00:30:15,080
Such a huge dining hall.

903
00:30:16,440 --> 00:30:16,880
By the way,

904
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:17,750
you seem to be acquainted

905
00:30:17,750 --> 00:30:19,240
with that rich young fella.

906
00:30:19,240 --> 00:30:20,440
I met him in Jingcheng.

907
00:30:20,440 --> 00:30:21,900
He is Xia Dajun's boss now.

908
00:30:22,720 --> 00:30:23,480
Xia Dajun?

909
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:25,700
How is Xia Dajun involved?

910
00:30:26,160 --> 00:30:26,830
I've explained everything

911
00:30:26,830 --> 00:30:28,190
about Xia Dajun to that rich guy.

912
00:30:28,190 --> 00:30:30,080
Now, he's just trying to chase after me.

913
00:30:30,080 --> 00:30:30,920
I guess he deliberately

914
00:30:30,920 --> 00:30:32,250
followed us here today.

915
00:30:32,790 --> 00:30:33,800
That explains it.

916
00:30:34,070 --> 00:30:34,920
All the other companies

917
00:30:34,920 --> 00:30:35,740
pay visits separately,

918
00:30:35,740 --> 00:30:37,670
yet he insists on sticking with us.

919
00:30:37,970 --> 00:30:39,030
I've asked around.

920
00:30:39,170 --> 00:30:40,440
His colleague
who's in charge of the bidding—

921
00:30:40,440 --> 00:30:41,720
you remember that bald guy?

922
00:30:41,720 --> 00:30:42,640
He's responsible for the part.

923
00:30:42,640 --> 00:30:43,590
But actually, he hasn't

924
00:30:43,590 --> 00:30:44,510
made anything great.

925
00:30:44,510 --> 00:30:45,200
He's just riding

926
00:30:45,200 --> 00:30:46,240
on Chengrong Tianchen's

927
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:47,270
coattails.

928
00:30:48,920 --> 00:30:50,110
Okay. Let's just be ourselves

929
00:30:50,110 --> 00:30:50,750
and ignore the others.

930
00:30:50,750 --> 00:30:51,310
That's right.

931
00:30:51,310 --> 00:30:52,170
Uncle, you see,

932
00:30:52,680 --> 00:30:54,960
today, the most lucrative part
of the project is actually

933
00:30:54,960 --> 00:30:55,890
the guest rooms.

934
00:30:55,960 --> 00:30:58,050
But renovating all of them
will take a long time,

935
00:30:58,050 --> 00:30:58,880
and we're in no position

936
00:30:58,880 --> 00:30:59,720
to front that much money.

937
00:30:59,720 --> 00:31:00,240
Yeah.

938
00:31:00,680 --> 00:31:02,240
Sixty-seven rooms.

939
00:31:02,240 --> 00:31:03,110
My goodness.

940
00:31:03,350 --> 00:31:04,440
So tempting.

941
00:31:05,480 --> 00:31:06,280
What a shame.

942
00:31:06,310 --> 00:31:06,810
It's okay.

943
00:31:06,810 --> 00:31:08,880
Other opportunities are open to us, right?

944
00:31:08,880 --> 00:31:10,440
Three large conference rooms

945
00:31:10,440 --> 00:31:11,790
and nine less big.

946
00:31:11,930 --> 00:31:12,840
Since it's a smaller bid,

947
00:31:12,840 --> 00:31:14,030
it should be easier to win.

948
00:31:14,030 --> 00:31:15,440
The same goes for the dining halls.

949
00:31:15,440 --> 00:31:16,680
Uncle, which do you prefer?

950
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:17,830
Wait. I don't understand.

951
00:31:17,830 --> 00:31:18,960
If the dining halls,

952
00:31:19,030 --> 00:31:20,090
conference rooms,

953
00:31:20,100 --> 00:31:20,960
and guest rooms

954
00:31:21,250 --> 00:31:22,550
are renovated by different contractors,

955
00:31:22,550 --> 00:31:24,700
w-won't they be of inconsistent styles?

956
00:31:24,700 --> 00:31:25,800
Then let's come up with

957
00:31:25,800 --> 00:31:27,900
a design plan featuring a unified style.

958
00:31:27,900 --> 00:31:29,400
Consider it our way to help the guesthouse

959
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:30,070
solve a problem.

960
00:31:30,070 --> 00:31:30,920
But why should we?

961
00:31:30,920 --> 00:31:31,680
If we not only draw

962
00:31:31,680 --> 00:31:32,640
designs for our own target,

963
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:33,440
and but also for others',

964
00:31:33,440 --> 00:31:34,640
won't that be a loss for us?

965
00:31:34,640 --> 00:31:35,590
Don't worry about that.

966
00:31:35,590 --> 00:31:36,920
I've planned it all out.

967
00:31:37,750 --> 00:31:38,550
That young man Gong Yang

968
00:31:38,550 --> 00:31:39,950
is hired by me to help out.

969
00:31:40,160 --> 00:31:41,400
Gong Yang, what do you think?

970
00:31:41,400 --> 00:31:42,730
Are you interested now?

971
00:31:46,540 --> 00:31:48,270
Hotels and guesthouses

972
00:31:48,340 --> 00:31:49,710
have the same focus:

973
00:31:49,740 --> 00:31:50,960
a coherent overall style.

974
00:31:50,960 --> 00:31:52,790
It seems we're adding a bit more
to our workload

975
00:31:52,790 --> 00:31:54,520
by producing a comprehensive scheme,

976
00:31:54,520 --> 00:31:55,350
but that extra bit

977
00:31:55,350 --> 00:31:56,270
will give us

978
00:31:56,490 --> 00:31:57,310
a big enough edge

979
00:31:57,310 --> 00:31:58,770
to crush our competitors.

980
00:31:59,240 --> 00:32:01,450
Yuanhui is young and not very competive.

981
00:32:01,450 --> 00:32:02,830
But if our comprehensive proposal

982
00:32:02,830 --> 00:32:03,630
is good enough

983
00:32:03,790 --> 00:32:04,680
to be adopted,

984
00:32:05,040 --> 00:32:06,440
won't we at least get a little share
of the profits,

985
00:32:06,440 --> 00:32:08,970
though the major part
will be taken by others?

986
00:32:12,010 --> 00:32:16,460
[Shengcheng Guesthouse]

987
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:14,600
Gong Yang.

988
00:32:14,920 --> 00:32:16,640
I know your major is oil painting,

989
00:32:16,640 --> 00:32:17,960
and you crave a career in the fine arts.

990
00:32:17,960 --> 00:32:19,750
But since your family is of modest means,

991
00:32:19,750 --> 00:32:21,640
you want to make money from this job.

992
00:32:21,640 --> 00:32:22,480
Ms. Xia, I...

993
00:32:22,510 --> 00:32:24,000
Making money is a very reasonable

994
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:25,310
and legitimate desire.

995
00:32:25,310 --> 00:32:26,750
Don't feel embarrassed about it.

996
00:32:26,750 --> 00:32:28,750
Small though our company is,

997
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:30,400
we highly value talent.

998
00:32:30,790 --> 00:32:32,030
We won't treat you as cheap labor

999
00:32:32,030 --> 00:32:33,760
just because you're a student.

1000
00:32:34,160 --> 00:32:35,780
As long as you draw the design renderings

1001
00:32:35,780 --> 00:32:36,940
as per my instructions,

1002
00:32:36,940 --> 00:32:37,880
I'll be happy to pay you

1003
00:32:37,880 --> 00:32:39,350
as much as an assistant designer

1004
00:32:39,350 --> 00:32:40,200
deserves.

1005
00:32:41,440 --> 00:32:42,240
I used to only do

1006
00:32:42,240 --> 00:32:43,440
paintings at school.

1007
00:32:43,570 --> 00:32:44,570
To be honest,

1008
00:32:44,760 --> 00:32:45,720
I don't fully undertand

1009
00:32:45,720 --> 00:32:46,780
what you just said.

1010
00:32:46,960 --> 00:32:48,010
But when I heard your idea

1011
00:32:48,010 --> 00:32:49,310
of winning a bid by offering a free

1012
00:32:49,310 --> 00:32:50,510
comprehensive proposal,

1013
00:32:50,510 --> 00:32:51,400
I found you utterly different

1014
00:32:51,400 --> 00:32:52,130
from others.

1015
00:32:53,240 --> 00:32:54,040
I've decided.

1016
00:32:54,550 --> 00:32:55,680
I'd like to work for you

1017
00:32:55,680 --> 00:32:56,740
and learn from you.

1018
00:32:57,200 --> 00:32:58,330
I'm just not sure if I can

1019
00:32:58,330 --> 00:32:59,730
meet your requirements.

1020
00:33:00,350 --> 00:33:01,410
Don't fret so soon.

1021
00:33:01,440 --> 00:33:02,590
I'll go over the specifics with you

1022
00:33:02,590 --> 00:33:03,770
when there's a general plan.

1023
00:33:03,770 --> 00:33:05,720
You don't need to prepare in advance,

1024
00:33:05,720 --> 00:33:07,270
because what I want...

1025
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:09,730
might not exist in this era yet.

1026
00:33:14,830 --> 00:33:15,400
Xiaolan,

1027
00:33:15,640 --> 00:33:16,200
let's go.

1028
00:33:16,590 --> 00:33:17,110
Okay.

1029
00:33:21,880 --> 00:33:23,810
Do you have to come this close to me?

1030
00:33:24,030 --> 00:33:24,550
What?

1031
00:33:24,550 --> 00:33:26,110
Do you even know how to drive?

1032
00:33:26,110 --> 00:33:27,030
-What are you saying?
-Hua.

1033
00:33:27,030 --> 00:33:28,110
You pulled up too close. I...

1034
00:33:28,110 --> 00:33:28,830
Hua!

1035
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:30,550
Didn't you hear him

1036
00:33:30,550 --> 00:33:31,590
asking if you know how to drive?

1037
00:33:31,590 --> 00:33:32,510
Be careful.

1038
00:33:32,510 --> 00:33:33,920
Fine, I got it.

1039
00:33:37,720 --> 00:33:38,400
Ms. Xia,

1040
00:33:39,310 --> 00:33:40,720
I wonder if I have the honor

1041
00:33:40,720 --> 00:33:41,980
to treat you to coffee.

1042
00:33:42,440 --> 00:33:42,960
Sorry.

1043
00:33:43,160 --> 00:33:44,400
I already have plans with my boyfriend.

1044
00:33:44,400 --> 00:33:44,930
Let's go.

1045
00:33:46,480 --> 00:33:47,200
Take care!

1046
00:33:49,200 --> 00:33:49,830
Bye bye.

1047
00:33:50,550 --> 00:33:51,510
See you later.

1048
00:33:55,240 --> 00:33:55,840
Take care.

1049
00:33:55,920 --> 00:33:56,550
Goodbye!

1050
00:33:57,350 --> 00:33:58,550
That young beauty...

1051
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:00,260
is quite interesting.

1052
00:34:02,440 --> 00:34:03,000
Mr. Du,

1053
00:34:03,270 --> 00:34:05,110
this guesthouse project
is no big deal at all.

1054
00:34:05,110 --> 00:34:06,910
We can take it all effortlessly.

1055
00:34:07,310 --> 00:34:08,710
Since it's a piece of cake,

1056
00:34:08,710 --> 00:34:10,710
what's the point in fighting for it?

1057
00:34:11,230 --> 00:34:11,760
No...

1058
00:34:16,710 --> 00:34:18,400
What? You don't get it?

1059
00:34:19,480 --> 00:34:20,110
Why not

1060
00:34:20,880 --> 00:34:22,480
just let Xia Xiaolan have it?

1061
00:34:35,710 --> 00:34:38,510
Mr. Du basically told us
to cut that girl some slack.

1062
00:34:38,510 --> 00:34:40,670
He changes girlfriends three times a week.

1063
00:34:40,670 --> 00:34:42,550
He wants me to do a favor for him now?

1064
00:34:42,550 --> 00:34:43,440
Not a chance.

1065
00:34:44,360 --> 00:34:45,159
Go get the car.

1066
00:34:45,920 --> 00:34:54,360
[Zhiyuan Law Firm]

1067
00:34:53,110 --> 00:34:55,150
You're Xiaolan, Cheng's girlfriend, right?

1068
00:34:55,150 --> 00:34:55,810
Yes. Hello.

1069
00:34:55,840 --> 00:34:56,280
Hello.

1070
00:34:56,510 --> 00:34:57,910
How did you get to know me?

1071
00:34:58,110 --> 00:34:58,800
Everyone

1072
00:34:58,800 --> 00:35:00,400
in this law firm knows about you.

1073
00:35:00,400 --> 00:35:02,530
You look even better than in the photo.

1074
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:03,440
Thank you.

1075
00:35:03,670 --> 00:35:04,440
You're welcome.

1076
00:35:04,440 --> 00:35:05,480
Well, just go ahead.

1077
00:35:05,480 --> 00:35:06,070
No one else is in there,

1078
00:35:06,070 --> 00:35:06,760
except Cheng.

1079
00:35:06,760 --> 00:35:07,360
I'm leaving now.

1080
00:35:07,360 --> 00:35:08,230
Okay. Thank you.

1081
00:35:08,230 --> 00:35:08,890
No problem.

1082
00:35:22,480 --> 00:35:23,140
Zhou Cheng!

1083
00:35:24,920 --> 00:35:25,630
There you are.

1084
00:35:25,630 --> 00:35:26,290
Have dinner

1085
00:35:26,400 --> 00:35:27,330
before you work.

1086
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:28,900
Or your stomach will hurt.

1087
00:35:29,150 --> 00:35:29,590
Okay.

1088
00:35:30,070 --> 00:35:30,670
Come here.

1089
00:35:32,110 --> 00:35:32,640
Sit down.

1090
00:35:34,760 --> 00:35:35,280
Sure.

1091
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:38,380
What delicious food did you bring me?

1092
00:35:41,800 --> 00:35:43,510
Why did you put my photo here?

1093
00:35:44,880 --> 00:35:46,110
When I first started working in this firm,

1094
00:35:46,110 --> 00:35:47,550
an older lady in the logistics department

1095
00:35:47,550 --> 00:35:49,160
relentlessly tried to
set me up with girls.

1096
00:35:49,160 --> 00:35:50,800
She introduced to me every single girl

1097
00:35:50,800 --> 00:35:52,660
she's related to or friends with.

1098
00:35:54,150 --> 00:35:55,130
That makes sense.

1099
00:35:55,130 --> 00:35:56,280
After all, who doesn't want to

1100
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:57,510
bring home such a handsome

1101
00:35:57,510 --> 00:35:59,310
and capable boyfriend like you?

1102
00:36:00,440 --> 00:36:01,480
I told that lady

1103
00:36:01,590 --> 00:36:02,760
that I already have a girlfriend.

1104
00:36:02,760 --> 00:36:04,230
At first, she didn't believe it.

1105
00:36:04,230 --> 00:36:05,280
Later on, she said

1106
00:36:05,960 --> 00:36:07,770
it wouldn't matter
as I wasn't married yet.

1107
00:36:07,770 --> 00:36:09,190
It wasn't until I put this photo out

1108
00:36:09,190 --> 00:36:10,520
did she finally give up.

1109
00:36:12,190 --> 00:36:13,550
Why?

1110
00:36:14,480 --> 00:36:15,550
That's because

1111
00:36:16,110 --> 00:36:17,030
my girlfriend

1112
00:36:17,510 --> 00:36:19,710
is such a beautiful and excellent lady.

1113
00:36:20,920 --> 00:36:21,840
She then even got worried that I might

1114
00:36:21,840 --> 00:36:22,630
not be good enough for you.

1115
00:36:22,630 --> 00:36:23,320
So she's been

1116
00:36:23,320 --> 00:36:24,980
teaching me how to please you.

1117
00:36:26,380 --> 00:36:27,910
Are all the other employees

1118
00:36:28,030 --> 00:36:29,160
of the firm away now?

1119
00:36:31,710 --> 00:36:33,000
Small though this firm is,

1120
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:34,120
it takes on many cases.

1121
00:36:34,120 --> 00:36:34,840
Everyone has

1122
00:36:34,840 --> 00:36:35,770
several on hand.

1123
00:36:37,480 --> 00:36:38,340
What about you?

1124
00:36:40,880 --> 00:36:42,140
I'm new here, aren't I?

1125
00:36:42,550 --> 00:36:44,400
I'm doing paperwork for now
and getting familiar

1126
00:36:44,400 --> 00:36:45,660
with everything here.

1127
00:36:46,820 --> 00:36:48,780
Look, these are of the same style.

1128
00:36:48,810 --> 00:36:50,030
They can be put together.

1129
00:36:50,030 --> 00:36:51,830
And these are of similar colors,

1130
00:36:52,150 --> 00:36:53,190
so keep them apart.

1131
00:36:53,190 --> 00:36:55,230
This way,
it's easier for customers to distinguish.

1132
00:36:55,230 --> 00:36:55,920
Attention to detail

1133
00:36:55,920 --> 00:36:57,370
is a must for street vendors then.

1134
00:36:57,370 --> 00:36:57,970
Of course.

1135
00:36:58,000 --> 00:36:59,920
There's a lot more for you to learn.

1136
00:36:59,920 --> 00:37:00,510
Hey,

1137
00:37:01,070 --> 00:37:01,960
I bought this yesterday.

1138
00:37:01,960 --> 00:37:02,510
But I don't want it now.

1139
00:37:02,510 --> 00:37:03,550
I'd like to return it.

1140
00:37:03,550 --> 00:37:04,230
Return it?

1141
00:37:04,710 --> 00:37:05,710
Let me see.

1142
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:07,510
Will you let me return it or not?

1143
00:37:07,510 --> 00:37:09,400
Look, all sales are final.

1144
00:37:09,400 --> 00:37:10,880
Don't I need to check the item
before it's returned?

1145
00:37:10,880 --> 00:37:11,740
This is a refusal, isn't it?

1146
00:37:11,740 --> 00:37:12,960
I'll turn to
the market regulation bureau then!

1147
00:37:12,960 --> 00:37:14,420
The market regulation...

1148
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:16,130
Here's your refund.

1149
00:37:16,170 --> 00:37:17,770
Don't ever buy from us again.

1150
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:21,330
Smarten up, lad.

1151
00:37:24,330 --> 00:37:24,890
Sis Bai,

1152
00:37:24,920 --> 00:37:26,670
this is no way to do business.

1153
00:37:29,530 --> 00:37:30,160
That guy

1154
00:37:30,180 --> 00:37:31,800
is a notorious troublemaker in this area.

1155
00:37:31,800 --> 00:37:32,510
He is very close

1156
00:37:32,510 --> 00:37:33,440
with some thugs.

1157
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:35,190
If I hadn't given him a refund today,

1158
00:37:35,190 --> 00:37:36,400
he'd probably bring a gang here

1159
00:37:36,400 --> 00:37:37,330
to cause a scene,

1160
00:37:37,360 --> 00:37:38,840
which would disrupt my business.

1161
00:37:38,840 --> 00:37:39,320
Look.

1162
00:37:39,550 --> 00:37:40,360
It's torn.

1163
00:37:40,550 --> 00:37:42,280
He's just too fat to fit in this.

1164
00:37:44,760 --> 00:37:45,710
I really don't want to continue

1165
00:37:45,710 --> 00:37:47,170
running a stall like this.

1166
00:37:54,590 --> 00:37:55,280
Look.

1167
00:37:55,670 --> 00:37:57,480
It seems the sales are going well,

1168
00:37:57,480 --> 00:37:59,030
but the profit margins are thin.

1169
00:37:59,030 --> 00:38:00,320
And we keep bumping into crazy guys.

1170
00:38:00,320 --> 00:38:00,920
Our business works

1171
00:38:00,920 --> 00:38:02,110
by making small profits
from quick returns.

1172
00:38:02,110 --> 00:38:03,690
All our money is hard-earned.

1173
00:38:03,690 --> 00:38:04,690
Rich boy,

1174
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:06,840
are you already exhausted
before we even get started?

1175
00:38:06,840 --> 00:38:07,800
No.

1176
00:38:07,920 --> 00:38:10,510
I did know the profits would be thin,

1177
00:38:10,590 --> 00:38:12,590
but I didn't expect them to be this slim.

1178
00:38:12,590 --> 00:38:13,190
That said,

1179
00:38:13,450 --> 00:38:14,400
if you guys can stick to it,

1180
00:38:14,400 --> 00:38:15,000
I can too.

1181
00:38:15,800 --> 00:38:17,440
Actually, I've been thinking.

1182
00:38:17,440 --> 00:38:18,070
After

1183
00:38:18,400 --> 00:38:19,710
I rent a shop,

1184
00:38:19,710 --> 00:38:21,400
what kind of business should I do?

1185
00:38:21,400 --> 00:38:22,200
I can't sell

1186
00:38:22,230 --> 00:38:23,830
sundry goods forever, can I?

1187
00:38:24,070 --> 00:38:25,280
Xiaolan, help me figure something out.

1188
00:38:25,280 --> 00:38:26,520
What should I do that will allow us

1189
00:38:26,520 --> 00:38:27,480
to take care of each other

1190
00:38:27,480 --> 00:38:28,940
in business in the future?

1191
00:38:28,970 --> 00:38:30,630
My uncle is transitioning into

1192
00:38:30,630 --> 00:38:32,800
a commercial renovation contractor.

1193
00:38:33,070 --> 00:38:33,880
I think I'll probably build

1194
00:38:33,880 --> 00:38:35,740
a career in that industry as well.

1195
00:38:36,150 --> 00:38:37,070
How about I start

1196
00:38:37,070 --> 00:38:38,070
a building materials business?

1197
00:38:38,070 --> 00:38:38,710
Some stores

1198
00:38:38,710 --> 00:38:39,920
near Renmin Bridge sell stuff like those.

1199
00:38:39,920 --> 00:38:41,320
But they aren't very big.

1200
00:38:42,030 --> 00:38:43,110
That's a good idea.

1201
00:38:43,370 --> 00:38:43,850
We can

1202
00:38:43,880 --> 00:38:45,150
start with a small store

1203
00:38:45,150 --> 00:38:46,370
and gradually expand it.

1204
00:38:46,370 --> 00:38:47,000
Then, we'll be able

1205
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:48,110
to form a building supply center,

1206
00:38:48,110 --> 00:38:49,000
which will be a one-stop shop

1207
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:50,860
for those with renovation needs.

1208
00:38:52,280 --> 00:38:52,840
Sis Bai,

1209
00:38:53,440 --> 00:38:55,500
is the goal so big that you're scared?

1210
00:38:55,510 --> 00:38:56,110
Not at all.

1211
00:38:56,440 --> 00:38:57,590
The bigger the goals are,

1212
00:38:57,590 --> 00:38:58,840
the more motivated I am.

1213
00:38:58,840 --> 00:38:59,440
Tomorrow,

1214
00:38:59,440 --> 00:39:01,190
let's go do some...

1215
00:39:01,280 --> 00:39:01,630
What is it called?

1216
00:39:01,630 --> 00:39:02,760
That thingy...

1217
00:39:02,880 --> 00:39:03,630
Market research.

1218
00:39:03,630 --> 00:39:04,510
Yes, market research.

1219
00:39:04,510 --> 00:39:05,440
Let's do it together, Wei.

1220
00:39:05,440 --> 00:39:05,970
Shall we?

1221
00:39:07,040 --> 00:39:08,230
I didn't realize it could so hard

1222
00:39:08,230 --> 00:39:09,550
to be a self-employed vendor.

1223
00:39:09,550 --> 00:39:10,840
All my youthful years

1224
00:39:11,120 --> 00:39:11,920
are being wasted

1225
00:39:11,920 --> 00:39:13,180
on such trivialities.

1226
00:39:14,630 --> 00:39:16,230
Remember who said youth was about
taking risks?

1227
00:39:16,230 --> 00:39:17,230
If you really can't manage,

1228
00:39:17,230 --> 00:39:19,230
how about I give Second Uncle a call?

1229
00:39:19,630 --> 00:39:20,840
Please don't.

1230
00:39:21,510 --> 00:39:22,770
It'll make feel worse.

1231
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:26,070
Xiaolan, why are you so optimistic?

1232
00:39:26,280 --> 00:39:27,740
You've never complained.

1233
00:39:29,230 --> 00:39:30,000
When these people,

1234
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:31,800
who I strove so hard to befriend,

1235
00:39:32,320 --> 00:39:33,630
are around, I always feel the urge

1236
00:39:33,630 --> 00:39:35,590
to give them some pointers
based on my knowledge

1237
00:39:35,590 --> 00:39:36,630
of the future.

1238
00:39:37,760 --> 00:39:38,550
Yeah.

1239
00:39:38,880 --> 00:39:40,280
I'm clearly the oldest,

1240
00:39:40,550 --> 00:39:42,950
but Xiaolan is the one
acting like a parent.

1241
00:39:44,920 --> 00:39:46,710
But I'm worried that I might try too hard,

1242
00:39:46,710 --> 00:39:48,640
say too much, and expose the truth.

1243
00:39:51,590 --> 00:39:53,990
Children from poor families mature early.

1244
00:39:54,590 --> 00:39:57,320
Actually,
I've been having a rough patch lately.

1245
00:40:18,320 --> 00:40:19,590
Mr. Yuan, hello.

1246
00:40:20,300 --> 00:40:21,220
You are?

1247
00:40:21,280 --> 00:40:22,440
I'm Xia Xiaolan, who's been asking

1248
00:40:22,440 --> 00:40:24,170
to rent that store on 27th Road.

1249
00:40:24,810 --> 00:40:25,550
That store...

1250
00:40:25,550 --> 00:40:26,840
I'm not declining your offer,

1251
00:40:26,840 --> 00:40:28,480
but the property rights are a mess.

1252
00:40:28,480 --> 00:40:29,810
We can't make the decision.

1253
00:40:29,810 --> 00:40:30,370
I know

1254
00:40:30,400 --> 00:40:31,890
it's co-owned by an individual.

1255
00:40:31,890 --> 00:40:33,110
Please tell me about this person.

1256
00:40:33,110 --> 00:40:34,710
I'll try to convince him myself.

1257
00:40:34,710 --> 00:40:35,800
Comrade Xia,

1258
00:40:36,030 --> 00:40:37,070
I find your determination

1259
00:40:37,070 --> 00:40:38,070
genuinely admirable.

1260
00:40:38,070 --> 00:40:38,600
However,

1261
00:40:38,800 --> 00:40:40,130
I really can't tell you.

1262
00:40:40,490 --> 00:40:41,110
If that person finds out

1263
00:40:41,110 --> 00:40:42,030
that I disclose anything,

1264
00:40:42,030 --> 00:40:42,560
I will...

1265
00:40:43,960 --> 00:40:45,020
Anyway, I'm sorry.

1266
00:40:50,590 --> 00:40:52,120
Who on earth is that person?

1267
00:40:52,800 --> 00:40:54,730
Nobody dares to mention him or her.

1268
00:40:59,230 --> 00:41:01,440
Gosh, it smells so good.

1269
00:41:03,920 --> 00:41:04,320
Mom.

1270
00:41:04,550 --> 00:41:05,630
I think I need to hurry up

1271
00:41:05,630 --> 00:41:06,920
and open the clothing stores.

1272
00:41:06,920 --> 00:41:08,400
Otherwise, when your cooking gets better,

1273
00:41:08,400 --> 00:41:10,330
I'll surely become too fat to walk.

1274
00:41:12,960 --> 00:41:14,320
This is for Granny Yu.

1275
00:41:15,670 --> 00:41:16,670
Ours is in the pot.

1276
00:41:16,800 --> 00:41:17,320
Okay.

1277
00:41:23,150 --> 00:41:23,960
Granny Yu,

1278
00:41:24,290 --> 00:41:25,660
I made pork ribs and steamed buns

1279
00:41:25,660 --> 00:41:27,150
stuffed with wild vegetables today.

1280
00:41:27,150 --> 00:41:28,030
I'll put them here.

1281
00:41:28,030 --> 00:41:29,150
Do have a try.

1282
00:41:34,190 --> 00:41:34,920
Granny Yu?

1283
00:41:36,800 --> 00:41:37,510
Granny Yu.

1284
00:41:50,670 --> 00:41:51,360
Granny Yu!

1285
00:41:51,880 --> 00:41:52,630
Granny Yu!

1286
00:41:53,590 --> 00:41:54,280
Xiaolan!

1287
00:41:54,960 --> 00:41:55,710
Xiaolan!

1288
00:41:56,550 --> 00:41:57,350
What's wrong?

1289
00:41:58,230 --> 00:41:59,560
Xiaolan, come quickly!

1290
00:42:00,290 --> 00:42:00,800
Xiaolan!

1291
00:42:00,800 --> 00:42:01,400
Granny Yu!

1292
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:04,730
She fainted.

1293
00:42:04,760 --> 00:42:06,000
Call an ambulance now.

1294
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:07,200
I'll go make the call.

1295
00:42:07,960 --> 00:42:08,590
Granny Yu.

1296
00:42:09,400 --> 00:42:10,110
Granny Yu?

1297
00:42:13,640 --> 00:42:14,670
I noticed a couple of days ago

1298
00:42:14,670 --> 00:42:16,290
that Granny Yu seemed low on energy.

1299
00:42:16,290 --> 00:42:17,880
She usually has tea in the courtyard,

1300
00:42:17,880 --> 00:42:20,010
yet she stayed in for the past two days.

1301
00:42:20,190 --> 00:42:21,000
This is my fault.

1302
00:42:21,000 --> 00:42:22,440
I should have checked on her.

1303
00:42:22,440 --> 00:42:22,960
Mom,

1304
00:42:23,400 --> 00:42:24,110
this is not your fault.

1305
00:42:24,110 --> 00:42:24,840
Don't worry.

1306
00:42:24,920 --> 00:42:26,250
Just trust the doctors.

1307
00:42:27,360 --> 00:42:27,840
Nurse.

1308
00:42:27,960 --> 00:42:28,550
Nurse,

1309
00:42:28,960 --> 00:42:30,070
how is the patient?

1310
00:42:30,150 --> 00:42:31,680
What kind of family are you?

1311
00:42:31,920 --> 00:42:33,280
The patient went into shock

1312
00:42:33,280 --> 00:42:34,330
due to ketoacidosis.

1313
00:42:34,330 --> 00:42:35,320
She has diabetes.

1314
00:42:35,320 --> 00:42:37,280
Have you never paid attention to her?

1315
00:42:37,280 --> 00:42:37,740
Auntie.

1316
00:42:38,550 --> 00:42:39,590
What did you just say?

1317
00:42:39,590 --> 00:42:40,590
She has diabetes?

1318
00:42:40,630 --> 00:42:41,230
Yes.

1319
00:42:41,560 --> 00:42:43,190
The patient's really old now.

1320
00:42:43,190 --> 00:42:44,070
As her family, you should...

1321
00:42:44,070 --> 00:42:45,150
Nurse, you're mistaken.

1322
00:42:45,150 --> 00:42:46,460
They are Granny Yu's tenants.

1323
00:42:46,460 --> 00:42:47,070
It's been less than a month

1324
00:42:47,070 --> 00:42:48,150
since they moved into her place.

1325
00:42:48,150 --> 00:42:48,960
Nurse,

1326
00:42:49,110 --> 00:42:50,800
make sure you try your best to save her.

1327
00:42:50,800 --> 00:42:52,460
We will certainly do our best.

1328
00:42:52,480 --> 00:42:54,240
The patient needs hospitalizing,
given her situation.

1329
00:42:54,240 --> 00:42:55,190
Now, go home and prepare

1330
00:42:55,190 --> 00:42:56,760
some daily necessities for her.

1331
00:42:56,760 --> 00:42:58,070
Then tell her family to come.

1332
00:42:58,070 --> 00:42:58,510
Okay.

1333
00:42:59,630 --> 00:43:00,670
You two stay here.

1334
00:43:00,670 --> 00:43:01,800
I'll go fetch the stuff.

1335
00:43:01,800 --> 00:43:02,150
Mom,

1336
00:43:02,490 --> 00:43:03,110
don't go home.

1337
00:43:03,110 --> 00:43:04,280
Just buy something nearby.

1338
00:43:04,280 --> 00:43:04,710
Okay.

1339
00:43:05,160 --> 00:43:05,880
Watch her then, you two.

1340
00:43:05,880 --> 00:43:06,280
Sure.
